/* History */ As the director of the US Army Air Defense Artillery Museum, I realized that there were two errors in this section.  Firstly, it identified the Redeye as the FM-43.  The correct nomenclature is FIM-43 for Intercept Missile, Shoulder Launched (FIM).  The second error is the reference to "Redeye II".  The Redeye I was in production from 1969-1982.  Redeye II was the name of the program that evolved into the Stinger program.
